properties.otherAdvice:
Changed traffic conditions for the Coffs Harbour bypass will be in place from Monday 16 September to Saturday 21 September, weather permitting.

  • Single lane closures will be in place on the northbound and southbound carriageways of the Pacific Highway between James Small Drive (south) and Charlesworth Bay Road on Monday from 7pm and 6am for pavement rebuilding and concrete barrier installation.
  • Traffic control with short intermittent delays will be in place at the intersection of the Pacific Highway, Korora School Road and Russ Hammond Close. This work will be carried out from 7am to 6pm weekdays and 8am to 1pm on Saturday.

Motorists will see extra truck movements daily as part of the construction project and the delivery of concrete girders. Please allow additional travel time.

A temporary speed of 60km/h will remain in place through the project work zone.

Motorists are advised to allow approximately 5 minutes of additional travel time.

Portable traffic lights will allow motorists to pass in one direction at a time.

Traffic controllers will be on site to direct motorists.
2 of 4 lanes will be closed in each direction during this time. Motorists can still use the left-hand lanes in either direction to cross the Sydney Harbour Bridge.
